-- GM recalls 16,618 imported cars in China
-- 
-- Wed Mar 7, 2012 8:46pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/03/08/us-gm-china-idUSBRE82704U20120308

 

 BEIJING  (Reuters) - General Motors Co ( GM.N ) is recalling 16,618 imported Chevrolet Captiva and Opel Antara in China to fix potential problems with the antilock braking system, China's top quality watchdog said. 
 The models were made between April 11, 2006, and November 9, 2009, the General Administration of Quality Supervision, Inspection and Quarantine said late on Wednesday. (Reporting by Fang Yan and  Ken Wills ; Editing by Chris Lewis)